<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><div><br></div><div>(Please see attached Myanmar translation)</div><div><br></div><div>We wanted to draw your attention to a book and film called 'All the Bright Places'. This is a young adult novel which has now been made into a Netflix film.</div><div><br></div><div>The main character in the story, Finch, is very troubled, but his mental health issues are romanticised. By the end of the story, Finch commits suicide. Furthermore, the parents and teachers in the story are portrayed as being ineffective and insensitive. We are concerned about how this story romanticises mental illness and suicide, and how it portrays the character's adult support network.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>'All the Bright Places' is rated as 14+ on Netflix and so certainly no children younger than 14 should watch this film. Should you wish to allow your 14+ children to watch this, we suggest that you watch it before your children, so that you can check the content first. If your 14+ children do watch this, we recommend that they view it with an adult present, so that your children can discuss the issues raised with you.</div><div><br></div><div>Kind regards,</div></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br><div><div dir="ltr" data-smartmail="gmail_signature"><div dir="ltr"><div dir="ltr"><div dir="ltr"><div dir="ltr"><div dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span class="il" style="">Charlotte</span> Thomas</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><b>Head of EYFS and Designated Safeguarding Lead</b></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><br></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
